<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00129</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT TO ALLOCATE FUNDS FOR POTABLE WATER ACCESS AND THE CONSTRUCTION OF WATER SYSTEMS IN ALL BARANGAYS, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates the construction and implementation of  the necessary water systems and water facilities on a per-area or region basis to cater to all barangays, the poorest  local government units and barangays having the highest priority, as determined by the DOH, LWUA, DPWH, and such other agencies that have data and studies on the matter. </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Potable Water Act of 2019.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ZUBIRI, MANUEL F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Madrona (000 2019-08-01)</td><td>2. Suansing (E.) (000 2019-08-13)</td><tr><td>3. Robes (000 2019-08-14)</td><td>4. Dalipe (000 2019-08-20)</td><tr><td>5. Delos Santos (000 2019-12-04)</td><td>6. Vergara (000 2020-01-28)</td><tr><td>7. Tan (S.A.) (000 2020-01-28)</td><td>8. Espina (000 2020-01-28)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC WORKS AND HIGHWAYS ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>